<%# Article hero: full-width cover image (Figma 05.02, node 510:22906 — 390×269).
    Routes through the same archive_cover_image helper as the card thumbnail
    so the hero and the card show the *same* illustration for a given article
    (cover_image when attached, otherwise the cycling archive-{1,2,3}.svg
    placeholder picked by content.id). The 390×269 hero and 290×200 card both
    use a 1.45:1 aspect ratio, so object-cover scales the same SVG cleanly
    between contexts. bg-shuby-blue-400 paints behind the image as a fallback
    band against load failures.
    Back button lives in the page-level floating wrapper in archive/show.html.erb
    so it persists during scroll — don't render it here. %>
<div class="relative w-full h-[269px] bg-shuby-blue-400 overflow-hidden">
  <%= archive_cover_image(content, class: "w-full h-full object-cover") %>
</div>
